q1.question: How can I have a package delivered?
q1.answer: Create an announcement with your package details, choose a deliverer and make the payment.

q2.question: What types of services do you offer?
q2.answer: We offer package delivery, people transport, airport transfers and home services.

q3.question: How are prices determined?
q3.answer: Prices depend on distance, type of service and urgency of the request.

q4.question: Can I track my delivery in real time?
q4.answer: Yes, you can track your delivery in real time via your client area.

q1.question: What payment methods do you accept?
q1.answer: We accept credit cards, PayPal and bank transfers.

q2.question: When am I charged?
q2.answer: Payment is made when the delivery is validated by the recipient.

q3.question: Can I cancel an order?
q3.answer: Yes, you can cancel an order before it is accepted by a deliverer.

q4.question: How does refund work?
q4.answer: Refunds are processed within 3-5 business days depending on your payment method.

q1.question: How do you verify your deliverers?
q1.answer: All our deliverers go through a verification process including identity and insurance checks.

q2.question: What happens if my package is lost?
q2.answer: We offer insurance covering your packages up to €500 by default, extendable according to your subscription.

q3.question: Are my personal data protected?
q3.answer: Yes, we comply with GDPR and use SSL encryption to protect your data.

q4.question: How to report a problem?
q4.answer: You can contact us via our 24/7 customer support from your personal area.

q1.question: How to create an account?
q1.answer: Click on "Sign up" and follow the steps. Email verification is required.

q2.question: I forgot my password, what to do?
q2.answer: Use the "Forgot password" link on the login page to reset your password.

q3.question: Can I modify my personal information?
q3.answer: Yes, you can modify your information from your personal area at any time.

q4.question: How to delete my account?
q4.answer: Contact our customer support to request deletion of your account and all your data.

faq.title: Frequently Asked Questions
faq.subtitle: Find answers to your most frequently asked questions

q1.question: How to create an announcement?
q1.answer: Log in to your account, click 'New announcement' and fill out the form with your request details.

q2.question: Can I edit my announcement?
q2.answer: Yes, you can edit your announcement as long as it hasn't been accepted by a deliverer.

q3.question: How much does an announcement cost?
q3.answer: The price depends on the service type, distance and urgency. You set your budget when creating.

q4.question: How to delete an announcement?
q4.answer: Access your announcements from your dashboard and click 'Delete'.

q1.question: What types of packages can I send?
q1.answer: All types of legal packages, up to 30kg. Fragile, valuable or dangerous items require special mention.

q2.question: How to pack my package?
q2.answer: Use appropriate and sturdy packaging. Protect fragile items and clearly indicate the address.

q3.question: Can I insure my package?
q3.answer: Yes, our Starter and Premium subscriptions include automatic insurance up to €115 and €3000 respectively.

q4.question: What to do if my package is lost?
q4.answer: Immediately contact our customer service with your tracking number. We launch an investigation.

q1.question: How to track my delivery?
q1.answer: Use the tracking number provided in your customer area or mobile app to track in real time.

q2.question: What to do if nobody is present for delivery?
q2.answer: The deliverer will contact you. You can reschedule delivery or designate a pickup point.

q3.question: How to validate reception?
q3.answer: Give the 6-digit code received by SMS to the deliverer to confirm proper reception.

q4.question: Can I change the delivery address?
q4.answer: Yes, before the deliverer picks up the package. Contact them directly via messaging.

section1.title: Introduction
section1.content: EcoDeli is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy describes how we collect, use and protect your personal data in accordance with GDPR.

section2.title: Data collected
section2.intro: We collect the following types of data:
section2.item1: Identification information: name, surname, email, phone
section2.item5: Identity documents for deliverer account validation

section3.title: Data usage
section3.content: Your data is used to provide our delivery services, manage your account, improve our platform and comply with our legal obligations. We never sell your data to third parties.

section4.title: Legal basis
section4.content: The processing of your data is based on the performance of the service contract, your explicit consent, and compliance with our legal obligations as a matchmaking platform.

section5.title: Data sharing
section5.intro: We may share your data in the following cases:
section5.item3: In case of legal or judicial obligation

section6.title: Your rights
section6.content: You have the rights of access, rectification, erasure, portability, limitation of processing and opposition. Contact us at privacy@ecodeli.fr to exercise your rights.

section7.title: Contact
section7.content: For any questions regarding this privacy policy, contact our DPO at privacy@ecodeli.fr or by mail at 110 rue de Flandre, 75019 Paris.
